
{% extends "task_base_layout.html.jinja" %}

{% set task_script = 'instruct_training' %}

{% block task_content %}
    <div id="task">
        <h2>Instructions for Part 1 (Practice section)</h2>
        <p>
            There are two parts to this experiment. Part 1
            is a brief practice exercise to prepare you for Part 2.
            Parts 1 and 2 work in exactly the same way.
        </p>
        <p>
            On each screen, you will listen to a
            <b>meaningless nonsense word</b>. You will
            then decide, based on how the word <b>sounds</b>,
            how natural it would be if it were a word of English,
            and give it a rating from <b>1 to 5 stars</b>.
        </p>
        <p>
            Some examples are shown below of nonsense words similar
            to those that you will encounter in the experiment, along
            with possible star ratings.
        </p>
